cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF 

The paper deals with the performance of a cooperative relaying protocol for large M2M networks, which involves communication between a large number of devices. This falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of slotted ALOHA as the MAC protocol, which is a common technique in control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical modeling and analysis to evaluate the performance of the proposed protocol, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.MA) and performance analysis (cs.PF).
